==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''adumbrātus'' "represented in outline", from ''adumbrāre'' "cast a shadow on", from ''umbra'' "[[shadow]]".

===Pronunciation===
IPA: /ˈædʌmˌbɹeɪt/, SAMPA: <tt>/"{dVm%br\eIt/</tt> <small>([[Wiktionary:Pronunciation_key|key]])</small>

===Verb===
